casebody.data:
PEOPLE State of Illinois, respondent,
v.
Darron L. WARREN, petitioner. No. 122639 Supreme Court of Illinois. November 22, 2017

Petition for Leave to Appeal Denied.

In the exercise of this Court's supervisory authority, the Appellate Court, Third District, is directed to vacate its judgment in People v. Warren, case No. 3-15-0085 (07/26/17), dismissing the appeal for lack of jurisdiction. The appellate court is directed to consider the appeal on the merits, specifically the issue of whether the amount of fines, fees, and costs assessed against defendant is correct.
